==Russian==
===Noun===
'''[[местный]] [[падеж]]''' (méstnyj padéž) {{m}}

# [[locative case]]
:N.B.&mdash; In Russian grammar, the '''locative case''' is often called [[предложный падеж]] ([[prepositional case]]), due to the fact that the once separate locative, vocative, and prepositional cases have for the most part merged in Modern Russian. However, there are still many words that show a distinction in the prepositional and locative forms...e.g., [[берег]] and [[дверь]].

